<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="K" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Knightly1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Knightly,</orth> adj. pertaining to a knight, chivalrous: <cit><quote>my k. stomach,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 1.191" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 191</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>chivalrous design of k. trial,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 81</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my k. sword,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.29.81" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 29</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the garter, blemished, pawned his k. virtue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.370" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 370</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>